<item>
            <title>[HBASE-2246] Add a getConfiguration method to HTableInterface</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-2246</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Right now there is no way of accessing the &lt;tt&gt;Configuration&lt;/tt&gt; object used by an &lt;tt&gt;HTable&lt;/tt&gt;.  This is annoying.  In my case I want to be able to access the value of &lt;tt&gt;hbase.regionserver.lease.period&lt;/tt&gt; of an &lt;tt&gt;HTable&lt;/tt&gt; instance provided by the caller in order to wait the right amount of time between my successive attempts to grab a &lt;tt&gt;RowLock&lt;/tt&gt; on a particular row.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I propose to add a new method, &lt;tt&gt;public Configuration getConfiguration()&lt;/tt&gt; to &lt;tt&gt;HTableInterface&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
